There are two versions of the algae. The “shell” pattern and the “crosshatch” pattern. Competitions will use the crosshatch version as that is what FIRST received. Unfortunately many teams received the shell version. There is a thread here on CD about how this happened.

We were lucky enough to have received one of each. In our testing, and I think similarly at some other teams, it seems like the shell version is considerably easier to grasp. This raises the possibility that if you only have/test with the shell version, you may be very unhappily surprised at your first competition.

[EDIT] As to the original question, we have not yet noticed any issues or a difference in durability (but we’ve pretty much quit using the shell version for testing).
